        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tts): sanitize summarized speech text",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #90364.\n\nTTS summarization now cleans summary-model output before speech synthesis:\n\n- reuses the shared assistant-visible text sanitizer\n- removes exact echoed source prompt blocks, echoed summary prompt instructions, and complete or EOF-truncated standalone echoed `<text_to_summarize>` prompt blocks\n- strips only prompt-specific leading summarizer preambles while preserving valid first-person and user-request summary prose\n- preserves usable summary content after colon/dash prompt preambles without dropping subject-bearing user-summary clauses\n- preserves valid inline mentions of prompt tags in summaries\n- caps the sanitized summary at the requested speech target length\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`src/tts/tts-core.ts` joined `TextContent` blocks from `completeSimple` and returned that raw string as `summary.summary`. Auto-TTS then assigned that value directly to `textForAudio`, so reasoning tags, model control tokens, prompt echo, or echoed original text could be spoken.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Long-response TTS summaries no longer pass hidden reasoning/control scaffolding, echoed summarization prompt instructions, echoed summarization prompt text, exact echoed source prompt blocks, complete or truncated standalone echoed `<text_to_summarize>` content, or control tokens through to the audio text candidate. The review feedback cases are also covered: legitimate first-person summary prose is preserved, valid first-person summaries that mention `key points` are preserved, valid summaries starting with `The user asked me to summarize ...` are preserved before periods and separators, bare `The user asked me to summarize.` prompt echoes are stripped, usable content after bare colon-style prompt preambles is preserved, source text containing literal prompt close tags no longer defeats exact prompt-block cleanup, summaries that mention `<text_to_summarize>` inline are preserved, and echoed prompt blocks returned in a later `TextContent` block are stripped after text-block joining.\n\nReal environment tested: Dedicated local macOS OpenClaw source checkout on branch `codex/fix-tts-summary-sanitization` at commit `4be97aa0e9`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm exec tsx /private/tmp/openclaw-tts-summary-proof.ts`\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the local OpenClaw source run:\n\n```console\n$ pnpm exec tsx /private/tmp/openclaw-tts-summary-proof.ts\nOpenClaw TTS summary proof\nsanitizedSummary=\"Concise audible summary.\"\nsanitizedOutputLength=24\ntargetLength=120\nleakedForbiddenTokens=none\nfirstPersonSummary=\"I need to keep the key points from today's review. The release moves to Friday.\"\nfirstPersonPreserved=yes\ninlineTagSummary=\"The docs mention `<text_to_summarize>` as a literal prompt marker. The release moves to Friday.\"\ninlineTagPreserved=yes\njoinedPromptSummary=\"Concise audible summary.\"\nbareUserPromptSummary=\"Deployment was delayed until Friday.\"\naudioText=Concise audible summary.\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The sanitized audio text candidate was `Concise audible summary.`. The proof input included summarizer preamble, `<think>` reasoning, `<|assistant|>` control token, tool-call XML, and an echoed standalone `<text_to_summarize>` block; the produced audio text candidate had `leakedForbiddenTokens=none` and stayed under the requested target length. The same production `summarizeText` cleanup path also preserved `I need to keep the key points from today's review. The release moves to Friday.` with `firstPersonPreserved=yes`, preserved the inline tag summary with `inlineTagPreserved=yes`, stripped a joined later-block prompt echo to `joinedPromptSummary=\"Concise audible summary.\"`, and stripped a bare user-summary sentence echo to `bareUserPromptSummary=\"Deployment was delayed until Friday.\"`.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Microsoft/MiniMax audio playback was not run because provider credentials and audio playback setup were not available in this local checkout.\n\nProof limitations or environment constraints: This proof exercises the production `summarizeText` cleanup path from the PR worktree with controlled provider text. It verifies the text handed toward speech synthesis, not the downstream Microsoft audio renderer.\n\n## CI / Review State\n\n- Review comments from ClawSweeper and Codex on earlier heads were addressed through `4be97aa0e9` by tightening prompt-echo detection, preserving text-block boundaries before cleanup, stripping echoed prompt instructions, preserving first-person summary prose, preserving valid first-person `key points` summaries, preserving valid inline prompt-tag mentions, preserving valid `The user asked me to summarize ...` summary prose before periods and separators, stripping bare period-form user-summary prompt echoes, preserving content after bare colon/dash prompt preambles, stripping EOF-truncated standalone `<text_to_summarize>` echoes, and removing exact echoed source prompt blocks even when the source contains literal closing tags.\n- GitHub workflows are running on the current PR head; current live status is available in the PR Checks tab. Local focused verification below passed on `4be97aa0e9`.\n- Codex autoreview was attempted locally after commit `18435b1380`, but the bundled helper's Codex CLI rejected the local config value `service_tier=priority`; this PR relies on focused local proof plus GitHub CI/review.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` in the dedicated worktree to hydrate dependencies\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tts/tts-core.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/tts.contract.test.ts packages/speech-core/src/tts.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-utils.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers.sanitizeuserfacingtext.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec tsx /private/tmp/openclaw-tts-summary-proof.ts`\n\nFocused verification passed across 3 Vitest shards: 2 unit-fast files / 165 tests, 2 unit files / 54 tests, and 1 plugin-contract file / 42 tests.",
